column1: Source: USDA National Nutrient Database for Standard Reference 28 slightly revised May 2016 Software v.3.7 2017-02-01
Nutrient data for: 15192, Fish, cod, Pacific, cooked, dry heat (may have been previously frozen)

(a)"Samples were obtained from 12 retail stores using a probability-based sampling plan.  Some fish had been treated during processing to retain moisture on thawing.  Untreated fish = 134 mg sodium/100g."
